OL,3,CWhat has AQoS axe got to do with
OL,4,Clicence fee deal?
OL,6,FThe news that the long-running show
OL,7,Fwas no longer in production emerged on
OL,8,FFriday evening and made the front
OL,9,Fpages of some tabloids.
OL,11,FOn first inspection, it may have
OL,12,Fseemed weird to link this story with
OL,13,Fthe BBC's financial situation.
OL,15,FQuiz shows and panel games are amongst
OL,16,Fthe cheapest and most cost-effective
OL,17,Ftypes of TV to produce.
OL,19,FIf the BBC simply cannot afford A
OL,20,FQuestion of Sport, then it truly is a
OL,21,Fbasket case.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G2/7
