OL,3,CWhat has AQoS axe got to do with
OL,4,Clicence fee deal?
OL,6,FBut it would be too simple to dismiss
OL,7,Fthis explanation as spin from the
OL,8,Fpress office ` a cover for the fact
OL,9,Fthat the revamp of the programme under
OL,10,FPaddy McGuinness proved to be a turkey.
OL,12,FThe truth is that with the pressure on
OL,13,Ffunding, commissioners are under
OL,14,Fpressure to spend very wisely.
OL,16,FAn automatic recommission for a long-
OL,17,Frunning programme which is no longer
OL,18,Fdoing the business is not a given.
OL,20,FResources have to be allocated to the
OL,21,Fprogrammes which are winning audiences
OL,22,For plaudits.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/7
